{
  "texts": [
    "The d = 6 SMEFT operators in the exact U(2) 5 symmetric limit have been classified in [18].",
    "In the CP-conserving limit, they consist of 124 independent terms.",
    "A concise representation of these terms can be found in table 1, and is subsequently made more explicit in tables 2-8.",
    "The effective Lagrangian we are considering can thus be decomposed asL = L (d=4) SM + i C i Q i, (2.1)where the Q i are the operators listed in tables 2-8.The following points allow to easily understand how the full SMEFT basis is reduced to the U(2) 5 -invariant subset, and clarify our notation for flavor indices: i Bosonic operators are not affected by flavor symmetries.ii.",
    "Non-Hermitian operators necessarily involve different fermion species, hence in the exact U(2) 5 limit they are allowed only for third-generation fermions.iii."
  ]
}